This topic explains how to install <%= vars.platform_name %> on AWS using Terraform.


## <a id="overview"></a> Overview

You can install <%= vars.platform_name %> on AWS with either the <%= vars.app_runtime_full %> (<%= vars.app_runtime_abbr %>) or <%= vars.k8s_runtime_full %> (<%= vars.k8s_runtime_abbr %>) runtime.

To install <%= vars.platform_name %> on AWS using Terraform, follow one of these procedures:

* [Install with <%= vars.app_runtime_abbr %> Using Terraform](#terraform-pas).
* [Install with <%= vars.k8s_runtime_abbr %> Using Terraform](#terraform-pks).


## <a id="terraform-pas"></a> Install with <%= vars.app_runtime_abbr %> Using Terraform

To install with <%= vars.app_runtime_abbr %> using Terraform:

1. Deploy <%= vars.ops_manager %>. For more information, see [Deploying <%= vars.ops_manager %> on AWS Using Terraform](/platform/ops-manager/<%= vars.current_major_version.sub('.', '-') %>/aws/prepare-env-terraform.html).

1. Configure BOSH Director. For more information, see [Configuring BOSH Director on AWS Using Terraform](/platform/ops-manager/<%= vars.current_major_version.sub('.', '-') %>/aws/config-terraform.html).

1. Configure <%= vars.app_runtime_abbr %>. For more information, see [Configuring <%= vars.app_runtime_abbr %>](./configure-pas.html).


## <a id="terraform-pks"></a> Install with <%= vars.k8s_runtime_abbr %> Using Terraform

To install with <%= vars.k8s_runtime_abbr %> using Terraform:

1. Deploy <%= vars.ops_manager %>. For more information, see [Deploying <%= vars.ops_manager %> on AWS Using Terraform](/platform/ops-manager/<%= vars.current_major_version.sub('.', '-') %>/aws/prepare-env-terraform.html).

1. Configure BOSH Director. For more information, see [Configuring BOSH Director on AWS Using Terraform](/platform/ops-manager/<%= vars.current_major_version.sub('.', '-') %>/aws/config-terraform.html).

1. Configure <%= vars.k8s_runtime_abbr %>. For more information, see [Installing <%= vars.k8s_runtime_abbr %> on AWS](https://docs.pivotal.io/pks/installing-pks-aws.html).
